This paper deals with energy management in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper proposes a new distributed dynamic topology control algorithm, which involves optimizing the energy consumption of each node in the network. This algorithm has implications for distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY), as it involves coordinating the behavior of multiple nodes in the network. The paper also uses an empirical model of energy consumption, which involves mathematical analysis (cs.MA) and information theory (cs.IT). Overall, the most likely category is cs.NI, followed by cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MA, and cs.IT.
